---
alwaysApply: true
---

Review this component as a senior UI engineer.
Context Files - Read before auditing:
- /styles/tokens.css - design tokens
- /src/lib/utils.ts - shared utilities
Quick Checks:
1. Next.js: Has 'use client' directive if interactive
(uses onClick, useState, useEffect, Radix primitives)
2. Patterns:
- Uses React.forwardRef for DOM element refs
- Has displayName property set
- Uses named exports (not default exports)
3. Types:
- Props interface exported and well-typed
- JSDoc comments on non-obvious props
- No 'any' types where avoidable
4. Tokens:
- No hardcoded colors (e.g., text-gray-600)
- No hardcoded spacing (e.g., p-4, gap-2)
- Uses design tokens (text-text-primary, bg-action-primary)
5. Utilities:
- Uses cn() from @/lib/utils for conditional classes
6. Accessibility:
- ARIA attributes where Radix doesn't handle them
- Icons have aria-hidden='true' when decorative
- Proper focus states, keyboard nav works
7. Stories:
- All variants have Storybook stories
- All sizes documented
- Edge cases covered (empty, long text, etc.)
Flag issues with:
- Specific line numbers
- Code examples showing the fix
- Priority (critical / recommended / nice-to-have)
